sentences: S. Sowmya (born 16 April 1969) is a Carnatic music singer.
She was awarded Sangeetha Kalanidhi title by Madras Music Academy in 2019.
Ph. D. (Univ. of Madras, 2012) for dissertation "A study of the effect of temperature variations on the pitch of a double-headed drum (mridanga)"
In 1986, she had her first performance at the Madras Music Academy, aged just 17 and thereafter performed there every year for 33 years.

She made her film debut as an actress in the movie Vaanavil Vaazhkai, which was released on 13 February 2015.
In 1998, Sowmya co-founded Carnatica - an institution dedicated to classical music & dance instruction, archival, talent search and other related activities.

On 3 February  2013, she led and accompanied Nithyasree Mahadevan on Nithyasree's return-to-stage performance (after a traumatic period in Nithyasree's personal life) at the TTK auditorium of Madras Music Academy, to observe Tyagaraja Aradhana.
